  <span id="freeText2075104809433485160" style="display:none">For Now, Forever (5 Stars)<br /> <br />Self-made millionaire Daniel MacGregor always gets his way, but convincing fiercely independent Anna Whitfield to marry him may be the challenge of his lifetime.<br /> <br />For Now, Forever starts out with a hospital waiting room. Daniel MacGregor has been in a horrible accident and his family is waiting to hear how he is doing…<br /> <br />Then we flash back to before Daniel had ever been married or had children. He is a young ambitious man trying to cement himself a wife, a woman to make him a home, a woman to have his children…when he’s sights set on Anna Whitfield he decides that she is the woman for him. The only problem is that she isn’t anything that he was figuring a future wife should be.<br /> <br />Anna is a strong-minded woman. She is going into her last year in medical school and her one goal is to become a doctor and be independent. While she seems fiercely attracted to Daniel, she also doesn’t want to become anyone’s wife and give up on her dreams. We can all tell that two strong-willed people can make for a very entertaining story.<br /> <br />I loved both Daniel and Anna, a lot of times with books it takes me awhile to warm up to the hero or the heroine but in this book that wasn’t the case. I liked them both from the very beginning and I was eagar to find out how their romance would develop. I loved how Anna stuck to her beliefs and her dreams for her life but I enjoyed watching Daniel romance her. I love how they can both be so stubborn but also let their guard down at the perfect moments to continue to feel that connection they can’t explain. I loved the development of their romance and the forward-thinking Anna had in living together before marriage.<br /> <br />Well, all in all I think you can tell that I truly adored this romance and the development it took on. We all know how it’s going to end up in the future but it was fun getting to take a step back to see how it all developed in the beginning. I also enjoyed how she didn’t leave us hanging from the initial story of Daniel and his horrible accident. Definitely a must read for any fan of Nora Roberts and the MacGregor Clan. <br /><br />In From the Cold (4 Stars)<br /> <br />Battling the British couldn’t prepare Minuteman Ian MacGregor for the fight he’s got on his hands to win the heart of Irish spitfire Allanna Flynn.<br /> <br />This was a very short read, only a little over 100 pages long, and took us back in time to an earlier view of the MacGregor Clan in Ian. He is fighting for the rebellion and barley gets away before taking shelter in a barn where his injuries prevent him from going any further…this is where he meets Allanna Flynn a stubborn and (for me) very entertaining Irish woman. Allanna helps nurse Ian back to health and in doing so the two end up falling in love. I really enjoyed this book, not as much as Daniels, but I still enjoyed it. I liked Ian a lot and Allanna really was entertaining for me even though her stubbornness could be a bit much at times…it was still a fun read! I would suggest this one for Nora Roberts fans and people who enjoy historical romances.<br /></span>
