  <span id="freeText9274472105595576550" style="display:none">For Now, Forever: When Daniel meets Anna, their tempestuous relationship begins. Set in an earlier time than the other MacGregor books, Ms. Roberts does an extraordinary job of showing how differently women who wanted a profession were treated just twenty to thirty years earlier. It is almost astonishing how fast the change occurred and how much we take for granted today. Anna, the calm one, has her moments of fiery challenge as she fights to win both Daniel and a career. Daniel, on the other hand, is his usual stubborn, arbitrary, arrogant self. As he learns that he can't have everything his own way, an endearing story unfolds.<br />In From the Cold: I expected this book to go back to nearly present times and was astonished to see that Ms. Roberts takes us even further into the MacGregor history and back to the Boston Tea Party days when the name of MacGregor was still proscribed by the English government. If I thought the relationship between Daniel and Anna was tempestuous, the one between Alanna Murphy Flynn and Ian MacGregor makes it pale in comparison. What a pair! If I could go back in time, I'd make this one into a movie with Maureen O'Hara as Alanna. Unfortunately I can't imagine any actor who could play the MacGregor! Either of them.</span>
